================================================================================
PURPOSE
================================================================================

This source code is published for one reason: so that anyone can read it and
verify for themselves that the Hypastack service does what it claims to do —
in particular, that files uploaded through the website are genuinely
zero-knowledge and cannot be read by the operator.

That claim is deliberately narrow, and the code shows why. CDN assets are not
encrypted; they are public by design and have only their embedded metadata
stripped. Files uploaded through the developer API are not encrypted either,
because no browser is involved to hold a key. Both are readable by the
operator. Verifying the zero-knowledge claim means verifying it where it is
made, and not assuming it extends to the paths where it is not.

Publishing the code is a transparency measure, not a grant of use. This is NOT
open source software, and it is NOT free software. Every right not expressly
granted in Section 2 is reserved.

